===Etymology===
From late {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|sausige|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} {{term|saussiche|lang=fro}} (compare Jèrriais {{term||saûciche}}), from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{term|salsīcia|lang=la}} (compare Spanish {{term|salchicha|lang=es}}, Italian {{term|salsiccia|lang=it}}), neuter plural of {{term|salsīcius||seasoned with salt|lang=la}}, derivative of {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|salsus||salted|lang=la}}, from {{term|sal||salt|lang=la}}. More at {{l|en|salt}}.

